Definition.WordDefinition: Metatarsal \Met`a*tar"sal\, a. (Anat.) Of or pertaining to the metatarsus. -- n. A metatarsal bone. [1913 Webster]
metatarsal adj : of or relating to the metatarsus; "metatarsal bones" n : any bone of the foot between the ankle and the toes
